text: Pasargad County () is a county in Fars Province in Iran. The capital of the county is Saadat Shahr.Gitashenasi Province Atlas of Iranاطلس گیتاشناسی استان‌های ایران At the 2017 census, the county's population was 30,116, in 8,813 families. The county is subdivided into two districts: the Central District and Hakhamanish District. The county has two cities: Saadat Shahr and Madar-e Soleyman. == References == == Other websites == Category:Counties in Fars Province
